17class CallPrinter final : public AstVisitor<CallPrinter> {
18 public:
19 enum class SpreadErrorInArgsHint { kErrorInArgs, kNoErrorInArgs };
20
21 explicit CallPrinter(Isolate* isolate, bool is_user_js,
22 SpreadErrorInArgsHint error_in_spread_args =
23 SpreadErrorInArgsHint::kNoErrorInArgs);
24 ~CallPrinter();
25
26 // The following routine prints the node with position |position| into a
27 // string.
28 Handle<String> Print(FunctionLiteral* program, int position);
29 enum class ErrorHint {
30 kNone,
31 kNormalIterator,
32 kAsyncIterator,
33 kCallAndNormalIterator,
34 kCallAndAsyncIterator
35 };
36
37 ErrorHint GetErrorHint() const;
38 Expression* spread_arg() const { return spread_arg_; }
39 ObjectLiteralProperty* destructuring_prop() const {
40 return destructuring_prop_;
41 }
42 Assignment* destructuring_assignment() const {
43 return destructuring_assignment_;
44 }
45
46// Individual nodes
47#define DECLARE_VISIT(type) void Visit##type(type* node);
48 AST_NODE_LIST(DECLARE_VISIT)
49#undef DECLARE_VISIT
50
51 private:
52 void Print(char c);
53 void Print(const char* str);
54 void Print(Handle<String> str);
55
56 void Find(AstNode* node, bool print = false);
57
58 Isolate* isolate_;
59 int num_prints_;
60 IncrementalStringBuilder builder_;
61 int position_; // position of ast node to print
62 bool found_;
63 bool done_;
64 bool is_user_js_;
65 bool is_iterator_error_;
66 bool is_async_iterator_error_;
67 bool is_call_error_;
68 SpreadErrorInArgsHint error_in_spread_args_;
69 ObjectLiteralProperty* destructuring_prop_;
70 Assignment* destructuring_assignment_;
71 Expression* spread_arg_;
72 FunctionKind function_kind_;
73 DEFINE_AST_VISITOR_SUBCLASS_MEMBERS();
74
75 protected:
76 void PrintLiteral(Handle<Object> value, bool quote);
77 void PrintLiteral(const AstRawString* value, bool quote);
78 void FindStatements(const ZonePtrList<Statement>* statements);
79 void FindArguments(const ZonePtrList<Expression>* arguments);
80};
